LDGINFO(1)                  User Commands                 LDGINFO(1)


NAME
    LDGINFO - An utility to control the LDG system and shared 
              libraries. Version 2.20 (formely SHOWLIB).

SYNOPSIS
    LDGINFO [options] [file ...]

PARAMETERS
    The command line attents for a list of options eventually 
    followed by a list of LDG-libraries. File is the name of a LDG 
    library. Options are :
        -h, --help : 
            display a help message,

        -v, --version :
            display the version number,

        -l, --ldg :
        	display the LDG configuration,

        -p, --header :
        -f, --function :
        -u, --update :
            these options require a list of one or severals 
            libraries specified at the end of the command line. If 
            the path of the libraries is not complet, LDGINFO uses 
            the LDG cookie to locate where the libraries are 
            stored. The extension of a library can be omitted. In 
            this case, a postfix '.ldg' is used.

            Option -p displays informations contained in the header 
            of the library.

            Option -f displays the list of functions avalaible in 
            the library.

            Option -u update the library : the library will be 
            copied in the LDG-path if its number version is the 
            last. In addition, if the older library is backuped 
            using its version number as file extension (eg: 
            screen.ldg version 1.30 is renamed as screen.130).

        -i, --inspect :
            this option examines all LDG libraries stored in the 
            LDG path system. Subdirectories are explored too,

        -i <pathfolder>, --inspect <pathfolder> :
            LDGINFO examine all files from the directory <pathfolder>,

        -t, -internal:
            display internal information about libraries loaded,

        -m, --manager :
            display information about the LDG-manager if loaded in 
            memory, this option is here for backward compatibility. 
            In the last version of LDG, library loaded by TSR and 
            by Manager are shared,

        -g, --garbage :
            perform a garbage collecting : unused libraries will be
            discharged,

        -r, --reset :
            reset LDG system : all libraries will be discharged. A
            LDG_QUIT message is sent to each client using these
            libraries. Use with option with many precaution (it is 
            used by LDG developpers for their testing sequences),

        -k, --key :
            LDGINFO waits a keypressed to terminate,

        -a, --all :
            cumulate options -l, -m, -p, -f,

    The following options address the ldg cookie ('LDGM'). When a
    value is changed, that affects directly LDG system, however these
    changes are not taken into account for the next reboot.

        --cookie-version:
            display the cookie version i.e. the LDG kernel version
            currently active,

        --cookie-idle [value] :
            display or set the cookie time idle value to 'value' 
            (in msec),

        --cookie-garbage [value] :
            display or set the cookie auto garbage collector time 
            to 'value' (in sec),

        --cookie-path [path] :
            display or set the cookie path where are stored the LDG 
            libraries,

    The following options address the TSR (LDG.PRG). When a value 
    is changed, the change will be take in account for the next 
    reboot. However, if you can use the LDG CPX, these switches will be 
    probably without action. These switches will be used in the 
    special case if you does not use a control panel.

        --tsr-version:
            display the TSR version,

        --tsr-idle [value]:
        	display or set the TSR idle time to 'value' (in msec),

        --tsr-garbage [value]:
            display or set the TSR garbage time to 'value' (in sec.),

        --tsr-path [path]:
        	display or set the TSR  path where are stored the LDG 
            libraries,

        --tsr path:
        	specify the location of LDG.PRG. The default location 
            is 'C:\AUTO\LDG.PRG'. This option should be placed be 
            before options --tsr-*.

DESCRIPTION
    LDGINFO is a tool devoted to handle your LDG system. It is a 
    command line program and an alternative if you does not use
    a CPX control panel. It could be call from a script during a
    boot in a Unix-style environment. With LDGINFO, you can :

        - inspect your LDG configuration (see -l,-t options)
        - configure the LDG cookie (--cookie-*),
        - inspect your libraries and update them easily (-f,-p,-i,-u),
        - inspect the LDG manager (-m),
        - change the internal default settings of the TSR (--tsr-*),
        - clean LDG memory and reset the system (-g,-r).

	Update a library with ldginfo is very recommend (see option -u).

    This version of LDGINFO is compiled with LDG 2.xx but it is
    normaly compatible with all version of LDG. Please, contact
    the author for any problems.

EXAMPLES
    List libraries available on your system :
        > ldginfo -i 

    A general view of your LDG configuration :
        > ldginfo -l

    Where are stored your libraries ?
        > ldginfo --cookie-path

    A way for a script to locate ldg librarie path
        > ldgpath=`ldginfo --cookie-path`

    Change the time temporaly garbage collecting value :
        > ldginfo --cookie-garbage 2000

    Print the LDG version :
        > ldginfo --cookie-version

    Display informations about MEM.LDG, a standard library :
        > ldginfo -p -f mem

    List libraries currently loaded and clients using them :
        > ldginfo -t

    Install or update a library :
        > ldginfo -u mesa_gl.ldg

    Clean LDG memory (perform a garbage collecting) :
        > ldginfo -g

